args: Wait, what?! But we were JUST\nback in the Halidom!
This is bananas! And grapes! Both of 'em!\nI mean, this could absolutely revolutionize\nthe distribution of goods!
How have we not set up these teleporter\nthingies up all over Alberia already?
Unfortunately, we can't. The teleportation \nability comes from a jewel that Alberius\nleft behind.
Well, that's a kick in the britches.
This guy thought the same thing at first.\nI mean, it'd be so handy to just pop from\none place to another like that, yeah?
But nothin' is easy in this hard old world,\nso shuffle them feet and let's finish the\ntrip with some honest walkin'!
We're off to Valzgald, the biggest\ntrade hub in North Grastaea!
Daaaayum, Nina! That rupie magic\nis no joke!
So the more ya earn, the stronger it gets?\nSounds made up, but I guess I gotta\nbelieve since I just saw ya do it.
Still, that was some serious power.\nJust how much HAVE ya earned?
Hee hee! I'm afraid I can't reveal company\nsecrets, my good man.
That just makes me wanna know MORE!
They're coming back around, everybody!\nDon't let your guard down!
You just let your buddy Luca take this one.\nNina's magic is great and all, but I'm no\nslouch myself!
And what kinda merc would I be if I let\nsome merchant do all the fightin'?!
Aw yeah! That's the good stuff!
Mess with the bull, and you get the\nLuca and Ranzal horns!
Gya! Look out! There was another one\nhiding behind that rock!
Phew! Appreciate it, Nina.\nYou're a real life-saver.
Aw, no worries. We'll just say you owe\nme one!
Uh oh. Now that's scary.\nYou know merchants never forget a tab.
Heh. Well, in any event, I'm glad that\nthe two of you are okay.
Let's keep moving. We're almost there.
I can't believe I'm actually standing in the\nbiggest trade hub in North Grastaea!
Oh, sorry. I was just, um...so moved\nthat I was speechless.
Say, {player_name}? If we're\ngonna be here for a while,\nyou mind if I go poke around?
I want to check out the city and make\nsome notes for future reference.
Of course. If you need anything, I'll be\ntalking with the head of the city about a\npotential exchange with Alberia.
We'll have things settled in about three\ndays, so let's meet back here then.
Gotcha. See you in three days!
All righty, time to scope out the local\nshops and take in the vibes.
Huh? Why is a sunny orange THIS pricey?\nIt's three times more than in the south!
Maybe it's the difference in climate?
Oranges are hard to grow in colder\nclimates, and the smaller the harvest,\nthe higher the price rises, which means...
I smell a business opportunity!\n...'Scuse me! Shopkeep!
What can I do for you, miss?
Why is this sunny orange so expensive?
Uh...because it's valuable? You won't\nfind a lower price anywhere in town,\nif that's what you're wondering.
Okay, so I'm actually a merchant visiting\nfrom South Grastaea.
If you want, I can introduce you to my\nsunny orange supplier from the south.
That would be wonderful! ...Er, assuming\nyou don't intend to bleed off all my profits\nas the middleman, that is.
Not at all! I'm hoping we can have a\nlong and fruitful relationship, so I'll\nmake it cheap.
However, I WOULD like to pick your brain\nabout the state of goods distribution here\nin the north...
Well, that's all the business taken care of.\nTime to head back south.
Well, you're certainly in some high spirits.\nI take it you had a good time in the city?
I had just the BEST time, and I'm so dang\nhappy I asked you to let me come along.
And I ALSO fell into a business opportunity\nthat's gonna lead to some sweet, sweet\nrupies in the very near future.
Bwa ha ha! Look at this kid go! She can't\neven stop bein' a merchant on vacation!
Right? But hey, since we owe you a debt,\nmaybe we can pay it back by helping your\nshop rake in the mad coin!
A debt...? Wait, are you talking about\nwhen I helped you guys during that fight?
Yeah! I know I gotta pay you back, so when\nwe get back to South Grastaea, I'm gonna\nhelp your shop get up and running!
You can count ol' Ranzal in on that too.\nBein' in debt to a merchant seriously\nweighs on the ol' brainpan.
Uh...but no! I mean, I know I said you'd\nowe me one, but you really don't have\nto do
Nope! Deal's done! You just leave it to us.

Rupie magic gets stronger the more you
earn, so once we help yer shop start rakin'
in the dough, you'll be blastin' chumps in
the face like an old pro!
Uh, but don't ya WANT yer rupie magic\nwhat to get powered up?
Yes, but it's... I mean... That's a very\ngenerous offer. Thank you both.
Then it's settled! When we get back,\nwe'll get right to helping!
